#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/firewalld-beginners.md:13
msgid ""
"A long time ago, I was a little newbie computer user who heard that having a "
"firewall was *supposed* to be super good. It would let me decide what got "
"in, and what got out of my computer, right? But it mostly seemed to stop my "
"video games from accessing the internet; I was *not* a happy camper."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/firewalld-beginners.md:15
msgid ""
"Of course, if you're here, you probably have a better idea what a firewall "
"is and what it does than I did. But if your firewall experience amounts to "
"telling Windows Defender that yes, for the love of all that is holy, your "
"new app is allowed to use the internet, don't worry. It says \"for Beginners"
"\" up top; I've got you."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/firewalld-beginners.md:17
msgid ""
"In other words, my fellow nerds should be aware that there will be a lot of "
"explanations incoming."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/firewalld-beginners.md:19
msgid ""
"So let's talk about what we're here for. `firewalld` is the default firewall "
"app packaged with Rocky Linux, and it's designed to be pretty simple to use. "
"You just need to know a little bit about how firewalls work, and not be "
"afraid to use the command line."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/firewalld-beginners.md:21
