#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/firewalld-beginners.md:32
msgid ""
"Well... there *are* graphical firewall configuration options. On the "
"desktop, there's `firewall-config` which can be installed from the repos, "
"and on servers you can [install Cockpit](https://linoxide.com/install-"
"cockpit-on-almalinux-or-rocky-linux/) to help you manage firewalls and a "
"whole bunch of other stuff. **However, I'll be teaching you the command-line "
"way to do things in this tutorial for a couple of reasons:**"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '1. '
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/firewalld-beginners.md:35
msgid ""
"If you're running a server, you'll be using the command line for most of "
"this stuff anyway. Lots of tutorials and guides for Rocky server will give "
"command line instructions for firewall management, and it's best that you "
"understand those instructions, rather than just copying and pasting whatever "
"you see."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '2. '
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/firewalld-beginners.md:35
msgid ""
"Understanding how the `firewalld` commands work might help you better grasp "
"how the firewall software works. You can take the same principles you learn "
"here, and have a better idea what you're doing if you do decide to use a "
"graphical interface in the future."
msgstr ""

